1 (c) Notwithstanding § 37–202(a) of the State Personnel and Pensions Article, an
2 individual described under subsection (b) of this section may transfer the individual’s
3 creditable service in the Local Fire and Police System to the State Police Retirement System
4 in accordance with Title 37 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article.
5 (d) An individual described under subsection (b) of this section shall make a
6 request to transfer service in accordance with subsection (c) of this section:
7 (1) on or before December 31, 2025; and
8 (2) by submitting to the Board of Trustees for the State Retirement and
9 Pension System a form provided by the State Retirement Agency for the purpose of electing
10 to transfer service under this Act.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 6 months and, at the end of December 31,
13 2025, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be abrogated
14 and of no further force and effect.

